by Valentine Z » Sun May 29, 2022 8:44 am

Gandoor wrote:See I can't fully blame people for spacing out the code, especially if they have a large table.

Like look at the code for one of the tables in my GBC storefront in GE&T
(Image)

That is a goddamn mess of code and it's honestly a miracle that I've never completely fucked it up while editing.

I actually really hope the new forum upgrade (whenever that happens) adds a WYSIWYG editor instead of having to rely solely on BBCode for this stuff.

If you would like, you can try stuff like Sublime Text or any other editor that takes out the new lines (\n) after you are done with each lines.

My way is a little... convoluted. I set a certain amount of columns, run an Excel formula through the cells, THEN take out the new lines. It's actually pretty damn headache-inducing. >,<

Here's how the Excel formula looks like for one of my projects (the one with the heights of the leaders):
Code: Select all
="[tr][td]"&TEXT(A2,"yyyy-mm-dd")&" "&TEXT(B2,"hh.mm.ss")&"[/td][td]"&C2&"[/td][td]"&D2&"[/td][td]"&E2&"[/td][td]"&TEXT(F2,"#,###.00")&"[/td][td]"&G2&"[/td][/tr]"
